<h4>Quick start for Reference search</h4>
<p>Type one or two terms or fragments of the 
<ul>
  <li>author, 
  <li>title, or 
  <li>publication details 
</ul>
<p>into the search and press Enter or click Search.  The Editor will try to find something useful.
<p> E.g.  <%= link_to('bent hook notes', new_search_path(query_string: 'bent hook notes', query_target: 'reference'),class:'blue',title: 'example search') %>
or <%= link_to('bent hook notes 1986', new_search_path(query_string: 'bent hook notes 1986', query_target: 'reference'),class:'blue',title: 'example search') %>
<br>
<p>Order of terms is not important for simple reference searches.
<p>Reference searching is a slightly special case - in most cases, order of search terms is important.
<p>See the information about the citation field (below) for an explanation.
